'''Bright's disease''' is a [[History|historical]] [[Scientific classification|classification]] of [[Nephrology|kidney diseases]] that would be known in modern [[medicine]] as [[Acute (medical)|acute]] or [[Chronic (medicine)|chronic]] [[nephritis]]. The term is no longer used, as diseases are now classified by their more fully known [[etiology|etiologies]].


